  <div id="text-content_6f3853a5-1080-4836-b64c-bffda2e7ddfd" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can create item banks in New Quizzes. Item banks can be used to store questions for use in other quizzes. You can use your item banks in any course where you have permission to create and edit a quiz using New Quizzes.</p>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open-item-banks" data-step-uuid="ef6d8560-6517-429f-927a-e316a557190d">
    <h2 id="open-item-banks" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open Item Banks</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/005/224/332/original/7d1b55e5-1ac9-4c21-8206-bfe13ce2ded5.png" srcset="" alt="Open Item Banks " height="242" width="167">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_d409bcc7-2f2e-4e07-a420-7747b84ffd0f" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In Course Navigation, click the <strong>Item Banks</strong> link.</p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong> </p>
<ul>
<li>You can also access quizzes from the Assignments page.</li>
<li>You can also access Item Banks from the New Quizzes Build page.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

